<br>
Dunno how deep we can go with this one good group. Most people will be level 60 or near, with good equippment, and I will try to make the classbalance as optimal as possible. With two-groups-can-do-the-zone I assume you mean this kind of groups?<br>
<br>
When I talked about a SG raid I envisioned something like four or five groups of people (mostly level 55 and lower) exploring the zone, but two high end groups would also make a fine raid in my eyes.<br>
<br>
In my eyes a raid is not defined by the number of people but by the playstyle. <br>
<br>
Raid: a hunt not for safe xp but for glory and maybe loot. Something that takes skill and power and don't make you kill the same mobs over and over. Doing a entire dungeon of mobs capable of killing you, that is a raid even if done with only one group. A small raid then, but still a raid.<br>
<br>
Camp: staying in the same spot and killing the same mobs over and over.<br>
<br>
Farm: killing vastly underpowered foes for loot or faction. This include blue mobs of you use multiple group to kill stuff that one group could handle.<br>
<br>
That about that.<br>
<br>
Can you please tell me a bit more about the zone in general and the bossmob in particular? <p>Love, Edeina<br>
